{"/service/ndnp/in/batch_in_fontaine_ver01/data/sn87055779/00517016688/1927032001/0081.xml":{"full_text":"BUSINESS OUTLOOK\nGOOD IN AUTO TRADE,\nSAYS FACTORY HEAD\nChevrolet President Scoffs\nat Idea That Industry\nNears Saturation.\nAn optimistic note on tlie spring\nbusiness outlook in tho automobile\nIndustry, discounting the \u2018saturation\npoint\u2019 bugaboo and pointing out\nfavorable conditions throughout tho\ncountry. Is sounded in a statement\nJust issued by William S. Knudsen,\npresident and general manager of\nthe Chevrolet Motor company.\n\u201cIn forecasting a continuance of\ngood business prospects for the\nspring months, I am perhaps in\nfluenced by the aspect of our own\nsales which have never been better\nIn the history of the company,\u2019\u2019 said\nMr Knudsen.\n\"As evidencing steady growth in\nautomobile production during this\nperiod, statistics Issued by the\nUnited States Department of Com\nmerce for the last three years cov\nering the six months from Jan. 1 to\nJune 3C are interesting. The figures\nfor these years follow.\n1924 .2,054,661\n1925 .2,173.525\n1926 .2,450,780\nTwo Possibilities\n\u201cWith these figures showing busi\nness on the upgrade generally, there\nare only two reasons which could be\nadvanced for a possible decrease in\naales\u2014first, reaching the Ho-callod\n\u2022saturation point\u2019\u2014and second, a\ngeneral decline in business producing\na reactive tendency in buying.\n\"ifo one has ever been able to\nadvance any reasonable formula for\nfiguring the \u2018saturation point.\u2019 The\n\u201ctwo or more\u2019 car trend is so pro\nnounced that former theories are be\ning constantly upBet. If wo knew the\ntotal area which would be occupied\nIf all cars produced were running\nwithin that area, making it lmpos\nefble for this space to accommodate\nany mere cars, some basis would be\navailable for figuring *saturatlon/\nBut aucb a situation Is Impossible\u2014\n\u2022ad we may leave the \"saturation\npoint* for the future to determine,\nInasmuch as the human mind will\nfind it possible to open up any\nbottle-neck of traffic congestion\nwhich might develop.\nas ior me general trend in busi\nness, country-wide reports show the\nusual spring activity is opening up\n20 days ahead of schedule. With the\nWinter fairly mild, marked only by\nseverity in spots, rapid acceleration\n\u00aef municipal and private construc\ntion operations is indicated. Farm\ning should start early due to the good\nweather and manufacturing opera\ntions generally are In excellent con\ndition.\nSmaller Profits\n\"Rapid turnover at smaller profits\nis the keynote throught industry as\nreflected by out country\u2019s business.\nWith this policy can only come a de\nmand for more transportation.\n\u201cThe shippers are demanding bet\nter freight service; the business\ntraveler is demanding better train\nservice and the automobile user is\ndemanding better service of his car,\nand the firm that is in a position to\nassure the buyer this better service\ncan have nothing but bright pros\npects for the spring of 1927.\u201d\nPPEXNIES INSIDE EGG\nBOSTON.\u2014Have hens become so\nashamed of the high price of eggs\nthat they have decided to give re\nbates? When Mrs. Lawrence Spiller,\nof Otlsfleld, Mass., broke an egg laid\nby one of her hens, she found two\ncents in it.\nBuick Stays in Style\nMotor car types come and go, just as motor\ncars do But the grace and distinction\nwhich characterize Buick always stay in style\nThey never become commonplace\nThe reason is, that Buick style is sincere, and\nexpressive of the quality that is in the car\nBuick owners never are asked to buy a car of\nexaggerated design, with lines which might\nbecome distasteful to the eye Buy a Buick!\nr t And you will always be proud of your car\nrHBN BETTER AUTOMOBILES ARB BUILT\nBUICK WILL BUILD THEM i\nv\n'X;\nTWENTIETH CENTURY OARAGE\nFELDMAN\n12S South. Lafayette Boulevard Maun 0530\nMain 0530\nEnglish \u2018Mystery S\u2019 Racing Automobile Brought to America\u2019s\nFamous Daytona Beach Speedway to Break World*s Records\nREAR 600 ILK\nASto engine\nU-QALUM\nTANK\nI\nSPEED\nfirrio\nbax nan v'\nJ3&\u201er A\nmart mom B\nAtSO VMM\nmean enuns\nBADIATOCC\ni\n1\nALUMINUM 6HELL\nHAW\ncunta\n\n\nCHAW\ndrive\nWQIKl\nCOUVUNO\nSHAFT\nREDUCTION\nfitVELCCASS\nTRAK$M&SGN\nOEAR&\nroCNTVHEEL\nIBSJAKK\nHere is the first sketch made pub\nlic in America showing: the construc\ntion of the English \"Mystery S\u201d raoer\nthat has been designed to go 220\nmiles an hour. The car has been\nbrought to this country for a try-out\nalong the Ormond-Daytona beach In\nFlorida, a wide stretch of hard\n\npacked sand, 500 feet wide and\nabout seven miles long. I\nThe racer is a 1000-horsepower af-\nfair costing $100,000 and built with\ntwo 12-cylinder engines joined by a j\nshaft. It is the product of the fa-\nmous Sunbeam Motor company of j\nEngland.\nMajor H. O. D. Seagrave, its driv- j\ner, is an American-born English j\nracer who has won several speed\nI\nmedals and has broken several rec\nords.\nThe car is like a huge cigar paint\ned red. It is 22 feet long and 0 feet\nwide and weighs more than 7,000\npounds. The engines consume more\nthan four gallons of gasoline a min\nute, or about a gallon a mile.\nThe tires are of special -design and\nhave to be attached by some special\narrangement to keep them -on at\nhigh speeds. The center of gravity\nhad to be shifted when It was found\nthe tail tended to rise off the ground\nwhen the car went too fast.\nAlthough the body is aluminum,\nthe chassis is made of heavy steel\ngirders to resist the tremendous\nstrain of speed and wind.\nCalculated to go 220 miles an\nhour, the Mystery S is said also to\nreach 75 miles an hour in low gchr\nand 140 miles an hour in second\ngear.\nEverything must be perfect on\nthis car, for there can be no allow\nance for errors, to make it safe for\nthe driver. It takes about four\ntenths of a second for the driver\u2019s\nhand to act on a message from the\nbrain. In that time this car, going\nat the rate of 200 miles an hour,\nwould travel 40 yards.\nTHE FLIVVER DOC\nl __ Si? c\\ ytnrTTH llnT\\\nCARE or THE GENERATOR.\nDoo, Tve got a erlcket under mj\nS hood. Tve located him and. now\nyou catch him. The chirping is In\nthe generator.\u201d\nThe generator Is one of the most\nImportant and at the same time one\nof the most neglected parts of your\ncar. The reason for this neglect Is\nthat the average motorist thinks\nthat the generator is a complicated\npiece of mechanism which Is liable\nto get. out of adjustment If it Is\ntouched by anyone not an automo\ntive electrician. The truth is that\nthe generator Is an extremely simple\nthing and any mechanic can explain\nIts functions to you so that you can\ngive it all the attention it requires.\nOil, of course, is as Important\nhere as it is in practically every\nunit In your car. In fact, It is so\nImportant that several makes of\ngenerators carry oiling instructions\non the name plates. It requires but\nlittle oil, but the oil film must bo\nbetween the bearings and the shaft\nat all times or excessive wear will\nresult.\nOn the leading makes of genera\ntors, the commutator Is encircled by\na steel band which seals It from\ndust and prevents excessive wear on\nthe brushes and commutator. This\nband should be removed once in a\nwhile for an inspectation of the\ncommutator and the brushes. If\nthe commutator 1? found to be dirty\nIt Is an indication that the brushes\nare not making proper contact with\nIt. In this case you should start\nthe engine and hold a piece of fine\npaper (not emery) against the com\nmutator as it turns. Do not be\nafraid to touch the commutator\nwhen it is running. Contrary to\ncommon belief, you cannot get\nshocked.\nThe squeaking or \u201cchirping\" com- j\nplained of to the Doc this week Is a\nwarning that should not be over\nlooked. Unless it is remedied the\ngenerator Is likely to overheat and\nthe wear on the brushes will he\nexcessive.\nHow to avoid trouble Is no puz\nzle to the man who knows Safety\nrules and uses common sense. But\nthere are many drivers who do not\nhave common sense. These weekly\ntips from the Traffic Cop are dedi\ncated not only to these groups but\nalso to the others. Even a careful\ndriver will benefit by a weekly re\nminder.\nBe careful when yon approach\ntwo or more people crossing the\nstreet together. Quite often before\nan approaching automobile one\nperson may stop and one go on,\nor they may go in opposite direc\ntions.\nFRENCH UNIVERSITIES\nIN NEEDY CONDITION\nBv International News Service:\n'PARIS\u2014Wanted, urgent, a Rocke\nfeller to save the great universities\nof France. Their situation is dan\ngerous. They are almost without\nthe proverbial French sou and their\nonce-renowned .libraries have be\ncome \"a shame and a scandal,\u201d says\n\u201cLe Matin.\u201d\nThe credit granted for the pur\n;hase of necessary books and peri\nodicals, although doubled since the\ntvar, is still ridiculously low, a bare\nmillion of francs for the five facul\nties of the seventeen academies in\nFrance. There are certain collec\ntions where 12 years of valuable\ndocuments are missing and prob\nably never will be replaced. Visit\ning foreigners and those doing re\nsearch work here are astounded to\nsee their requests returned with the\nlittle note, \"Not in the library,\"\nSHRAKE BEFORE TAKING!\nPORTLAND, Me.\u2014For selling a\nthree-layer patent medicine com\nbination, Ivouls Pelletier was sen\ntenced to 14 months in pall at Bid\ndeford. The top layer -was cod liver\noil, the middle honey and the bottom\nrum. Customers, by pushing a\nstraw through the top layer, could\nget two drinks of rum and honey for\n$1, without tasting the oil.\nJNEKU rKiSliAUTlUN\nIN SPRING DRIVING\nC. H. Kryder Warns Autoists\nJliat Thin Mud Coating\non Road is Hazardous.\ni\ni\n\n1\nI\nSpring driving requires its special\nprecautions as wel las winter car\noperation,, but the motorist who has\nbeen forced to exercise restraint for\nthe more severe months of the year\nmay be inclined to ignore the need\nfor further care. This point is raised\nby C. H. Kryder. manager of St.\nJoseph county branch of Chicago\nMotor ciub, who points out that un-\nder certain inevitable seasonal condi-\ntions, roads and streets in Spring\ntime can be just as treacherous as\nthose of winter.\n\u201cThe road that Is dangerous in\nwinter, because it is covered with\nice or snow, may be just as much a\nmenace to safety during the rainy\nspring months when a thin film ot\nmud covers the highway,\u201d says Mr.\nKryder.\n\u201cAs compared with driving over\na snowy or icy road, it seems mere\nchild\u2019s play to operate a car over\none that merely is wet with rain.\nHowever, during spring, the wet\nroad usually is made hazardous by\nthe thin film of mud that works over\nit when the ground begins to thaw\nand there seems to be no bottom to\n\u201cThe American Automobile as*o\u00bb\nIation, with which this club is af\niliated, In its far-reaching surveys\nnto accident Causes has found that\nho hard-surfaced highway which Is\nightly coated with mud is a fertile\nactor in producing mishaps. It has^\nhewn that the well-advised driver^\nnakos the necessary concessions to\niafety under such circumstances by\necognizing the potential danger of\nhe highway.\n\"It is well to remember that the\n(ver-dangerous front-wheel skid, as\nveil as the sliding of the rear wheels,\na possible on the road that lies\njeneath a thin film of mud.\u201d\n\u201cWAR DANCE\u201d\u2019BRINGS WOE.\nNEW YORK.\u2014 His war dance\nlaving gene unappreciated at a\nirowded corner, Chief White Eagle,\nCherokee, 39 years old. said in\nEssex Market court yesterday, \u201cI\u2019m\ndirough with New York and New\ni'ork tire water forever. Send me\nsack to Oklahoma.\u201d Suggesting that\n:he words of the request would\nmake an excellent title for a popu\nuar song, the magistrate suspended\nsentence on the charge of disorder\nly conduct.\nPROBE BRINGS CONTRIBU\nTIONS!\nBIDDLEFORD, Me. A \u201ccon\nscience found\u201d that eventually\nreached $4,000 started accumulating\nsoon after state authorities started,\ntheir audit of the city's books. The\nconscience fund paid for the inves\ntigation into tile civic affairs.\nTRIPLEWEAR\n8nu Two Labor Cotta\nLasts Three Times aa Long\nPROVEN PRODUCT OF\nENGINEERING ABILITY\nGreeter Than It* Name\nTRANSMISSION LININO\nFOR\nALL\nW\nFORDS\nORLD\nIDE.\nONDER\n$2.25.\nPer Set\nKnown the world over. Million* now in use.\nBRANDED ^.h \u201cCROWN OF PERFECTION\u201d\nThe MAGIC performance of this WIZARD Transmission Lining reduce a strain on drums,\ngears and axles, and saves tires and fuel. Fleet owners a surprise for you also.\nThe easy start on steep hills and smooth getaway is amazing; works like an electric motor.\nThousands of minute oil pockets in each band. An assured smooth stop.\nTRIPLEWEAR SATISFIES WHERE ALL OTHERS HAVE FAILED\nFollow Directions for Installing sod Adjusting.\nMAKE IT TRIPLE WEAR. ACCEPT NO OTHER.\nDelia\u2014 everywhere have it. Mammoth distribution featured by Jobbers\nDURWYLLAN COMPANY Inc., Mfrs. Ne\nThe Only\nFull-Sized Car at\nthese Prices Giving Such\nPerformance and Luxury\nSEDAN\n(BhutnztmD\n$830\nf. o. b. Detroit\n50 miles and more an j\nhour.\n5 to 25 miles in 8\nseconds.\n25 miles to the gallon.\nFull-sized, with ample\nseating capacity for\nadult passengers.\nMohair plush uphol\nstery.\nYou can prove by demonstration\nof performance that the Chrysler\n\u201c50\u201d\u2014with its 50 miles and more\nan hour, 5 to 25 miles in 8 seconds,\n25 miles to the gallon, marked\nease of handling and consistently\nsmooth operation at all speeds\u2014\nis in a brilliant class of its own\nwhich no others have yet ap\nproached.\nSecond, because the Chrysler \u201c50\u201d\nreveals at a glance\u2014in its full-sized\nample seating capacity for five\npassengers, its smart, low-swung\nlines and beauty of color harmony\n\u2014value in such startling contrast\nto all other fours and sixes in\nor near the w50\u201d price division as\nto automatically determine your\ndecision.\nCoupe, $750; Coach, $780. Roadster, (with Rum*\nhU Seat), $795; Sedan,$830; Landau Sedan, $885.\nAll prices f. o. b. Detroit, subject to current\nFederal excise tax.\nr\nAll Chrysler Cars are protected against theft\nunder the Fedco System.\n\nAH Chrysler dealers are in a position to extend\ndie convenience of time payments. Ask about\nChrysler\u2019s attractive plan.\nCHRYSLER\nCHRYSLER MODEL NUMBERS MEAN MILE\nMOULDER MOTOR CO., South Bend, Indiana\nDistributors\nCODDENS GARAGE\u2014MISHAWAKA, IND.\n\u2022Oth Ceatorjr Chirac* Xlkhart\nA. C. Glelow Motor Sale*.\nt MIchltMi City\ni St* Colltwm florae*.UPtrtt\nDowning* Oarac*.. Talparalaa\nMala Oarac* Swuriiar\nBlunt A Bonita AtMonOlo\nZellon 4k Zeller* Wbuuaae\nD. Hottn Culver\nUord Taylor ..Walkerton\nNorth liberty Bile 4k Conarete Co.\nNorth Liberty\nTruk 4. Veetely North Jadeou\nBrtran Auto Sales Bmm\nBby Ante Sales Viktrua\nU. 8. Pletoher .Nappaaeo\nBonrbon Ante Sales Boar bo a\nClyde J. easterner.. Goshen\nB. C. Herecher. Warsaw","height":"31896","width":"24512"}}
